Corporal David Hawkins, a Reservist from London, Ontario, with post-traumatic stress disorder, was released from the military despite his request to stay for another year to receive a fully indexed retirement.
His case came after that of Corporal Glen Kirkland, who said before a parliamentary committee last month that he had been pushed out before he was ready because he did not meet the rule of universality of service.
Mr. Hawkins pointed out that a soldier could be prepared to leave, with plans and consultation sessions, but that this was totally different from wanting to leave the ranks.
