After ten days of scandal, revelations and denials between the United States and its European allies, this is the first time an American government official has explicitly admitted controversial practices in the NSA's interception of communications and data in Europe.
"In some cases, I grant it to you, as the President has done, some of these actions have gone too far and we will make sure that it does not happen again in the future," John Kerry said at a conference in London in which he participated since Washington on Thursday 31 October via video link.
