Referring to the attacks of 11 September 2001, the Madrid attacks of March 2004 and the London attacks of July 2005, John Kerry assured that the American authorities had since thwarted many plans for attacks, through interception of communications and the collection of information.
"We have effectively prevented aircraft from falling, buildings from exploding, and people from being murdered, because we were able to be aware of these projects," argued the head of American diplomacy.
And, John Kerry told Europeans, "I assure you that innocent people have not been deceived in this process."
