But in its opening statement to the Commission, the YMCA stated that it "had never had to deal with a problem of sexual assault on children within its organization."
General Manager Phillip Hare was questioned about two cases: a YMCA employee was charged with child pornography offences and a physical education instructor at the YMCA Caringbah Hall was convicted of sexual assault on children in the centre where he worked in 1991.
